            <div id="stability" class="tab-pane">
                <h2>Organizational Stability Index (OSI) & Key Events</h2>
                <p>The OSI is a proprietary, blended metric combining factors like Executive Tenure, Key Contract Wins/Losses, Stock Performance Volatility, and Major Reorganization Frequency.</p>

                <div class="org-stability">
                    <div>
                        <h3>Booz Allen Hamilton OSI (Internal Score)</h3>
                        <span class="stability-score">8.5 / 10</span>
                        <p><strong>Rationale:</strong> High executive tenure and robust Remaining Performance Obligations (RPO), balanced against the inherent complexity of navigating major federal budget shifts and competitive protests.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>Competitor Comparison (Simulated OSI)</h3>
                        <ul class="competitor-list">
                            <li><strong>Leidos:</strong> 7.8/10 (Large, often M&A-driven scale introduces integration volatility.)</li>
                            <li><strong>SAIC:</strong> 7.0/10 (Recent portfolio shifts and contract losses/wins create higher instability.)</li>
                            <li><strong>CACI:</strong> 8.2/10 (Strong performance and focused technology/product wins provide significant internal stability.)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2 style="margin-top: 40px;">Key Events (Last 3 Years)</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Acquisition of EverWatch (2022):</strong> Significant move to bolster **National Security** capabilities, successfully concluding a contentious DOJ antitrust review.</li>
                    <li><strong>NSA FocusedFox Contract Protest (2023):</strong> BAH protested the $2.4B NSA contract awarded to CACI, underscoring fierce competition and commitment to retaining critical Intelligence Community market share.</li>
                    <li><strong>Global HQ Relocation Announcement (2025/2027):</strong> Major commitment to modernizing physical infrastructure to support advanced tech workforce and capabilities.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

